      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">9/9/74. ¶  ¶ Last night, dear Mr Ramsay, I got your two letters of the 3th &amp; 4th, ¶ Letters not found. ¶  ¶ and feel ¶  ¶ delighted ¶  ¶ at the prospect of your getting off a collector. ¶ See M to E. ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.09.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9/9/74.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Last night, dear Mr Ramsay, I got your two letters of the 3th &amp; 4th,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Letters not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and feel<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">delighted</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at the prospect of your getting off a collector.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to E. Ramsay, 1 September 1874.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will of course pay towards the expense, and feel sure you will get fully reimbursed for your own part by what he brings. You should however telegraph to Capt Nares,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Captain of the oceanographic expedition vessel, HMS<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Challenger</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and solicit, that at least<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one alpine</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>excursion under protection of the naval force should be arranged! It would likely be only a pick nick on a large scale.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Even if you got a small steamer of your own, you could not with<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">safely</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>venture into the mountainous high regions, for it would require a strong party both on land and on the vessel.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I found out, when Mr Hills palm fruits arrived, that his supposed Cocos! is an<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Areca</hi>
               </seg>, near the common Indian Betel nut (A. Catechu),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and his supposed Areca is a true Kentia. It is singular, that he should venture to send descriptions almost of no diagnostic value and on such ill digested data, as he obtained, into an official report.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hill (1874), p. 6.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>To protect him to some extent, I have placed his name along with mine as authority of the Normanby palm,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Hill's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Cocos normanbyi</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was transferred to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Areca normanbyi</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>, attrributed to 'Hill et Mueller' as authors, in B74.09.02, p. 235. On the same page M transferred Hill's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Areca minor</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Kentia minor</seg>, without joint authorship.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>so that his dedication may not be destroyed; and that is more than likely any one else would have done for him! Pray do<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>mention this to any one, until<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>you get the new number of the Fragmenta, which is printed, but not yet issued. For when I showed Mr Hill that his supposed Stenocarpus was an Oreocallis,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he at once seized publicly on the information without any acknowledgement whatsoever!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Hill described<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Oreocallis wickhami</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>W.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hill (1874), p. 6.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>And he may do so in this instance again. But — please — keep this letter, because the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">next</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>post may bring him letters from Dr Hooker, correcting his errors concerning these palms, and then it is well, that you could show what my independent opinion on the subject had been, though I saw only fruits (no male flowers) of this palm.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your Pterostylis is what I with Mr Bentham have regarded as a var.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">magniflora</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of P. curta. Dr Woolls sent this particular variety from Paramatta. I found it myself in 1855 on the Brisbane River and Leichhardt found it also somewhere in N. S. Wales. Whether on the fresh plant specific differences can be pointed out in comparison with P. curta<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>you or Mr Fitzgerald have ample means of ascertaining. The flowers are much like those of P. Banksii from N.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Z., but not the leaves.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As Mr Fitzgerald is a monographer of the N.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>S<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>W. orchids it will be best to place<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>material from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">within</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>N. S Wales boundaries at<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">his</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>disposal<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Robert Fitzgerald was had been preparing and exhibiting drawings of Australian orchids since at least<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1871<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Colonial Exhibition (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Empire</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Sydney), 22 August 1871, p. 3, erroneously named as 'A. D. Fitzgerald'); vol. 1, part 1 of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Fitzgerald (1875-1894)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>dated<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>July 1875 (see review,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney morning herald</seg>, 21 July 1875, p. 3).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A fruit specimen of Corysanthes would be interesting. But really what is all that in comparison to New Guinea new plants, including doubtless masses of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">terrestrial</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>orchids just now in flower of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Australian</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>type.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I wished I could go myself. Have you any precise date, when the Challenger will be at Cape York &amp; how long she will continue her researches at New Guinea?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You speak about an enclosed parasitic plant; it is however not in your letter; if it is the "horsehair" plant or as some call it the "negro-hair" then I have never seen its fructifications.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope that as you belong to a younger generation than myself, that you will soon be restored to health.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I could not think of communicating with the Journal, which you mention after its outrageous behavior towards me, unless it reversed its tactics completely concerning me.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Journal not identified.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Your best plan is to communicate any such information yourself to any of the two Sydney weekly papers,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>both of which are very friendly to me. Can not Capt Goodenough<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>James Goodenough.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>be induced to send ye[t] again a ship for a short time for mountain ascents to N Guinea<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">I</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>would go in her then if allowed! and you could be my companion or anyone you choose.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Areca<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Catechu</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Cocos</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Corysanthes</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Kentia</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Oreocallis</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Pterostylis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Banksii</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Pterostylis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>curta<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: normal; ">var<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>magniflora</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Stenocarpus</p>
         </div>
      </body>
